# Statistics Boxing Plan

## Goal Description
The user wants the statistics values (Active Habits, Total Checks) to be "inside a box". I will interpret this as giving each statistic item its own visual container styling (background, border-radius) within the parent card, effectively separating them visually.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.css)
- Update `.stat-item` to have:
    - `background-color`: `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5)` or similar.
    - `border-radius`: `12px` or similar.
    - `padding`: `10px` or `15px`.
    - `box-shadow`: subtle shadow to give depth if needed.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Navigate to `/stats`.
2.  Check that "Active Habits" and "Total Checks" are now contained within their own visible boxes inside the main card.
